00:15:02,935 --> 00:15:04,937
it really helps me
to pray about it.

261
00:15:04,937 --> 00:15:06,438
[Scoffs]
Pray? Yeah.

262
00:15:06,438 --> 00:15:09,525
What are we supposed
to pray for, exactly?

263
00:15:09,525 --> 00:15:11,527
Dear God...

264
00:15:11,527 --> 00:15:13,529
don’t take Tyler.

265
00:15:14,029 --> 00:15:15,531
You have Dad.

266
00:15:15,531 --> 00:15:16,865
Isn’t that enough?

267
00:15:17,116 --> 00:15:19,001
Oh, Ben.

268
00:15:19,201 --> 00:15:20,786
Prayer is just
telling God

269
00:15:20,786 --> 00:15:22,288
what’s in your heart

270
00:15:22,288 --> 00:15:23,789
and asking Him
to help you with it.

271
00:15:23,789 --> 00:15:25,791
Well, maybe I don’t want
to tell God

272
00:15:25,791 --> 00:15:27,793
what’s in my heart.

273
00:15:30,296 --> 00:15:32,598
I’m afraid to ask God
to help Tyler.

274
00:15:32,848 --> 00:15:34,850
I mean,
what if He doesn’t?

275
00:15:37,303 --> 00:15:38,304
No, I can’t.

276
00:15:38,804 --> 00:15:40,306
Come on. Come on.

277
00:15:43,309 --> 00:15:45,311
Dear Heavenly Father...

278
00:15:45,694 --> 00:15:47,279
TYLER: "Dear God...

279
00:15:47,279 --> 00:15:49,281
"how many people
are in heaven?

280
00:15:49,281 --> 00:15:50,783
"Must be a lot.

281
00:15:50,783 --> 00:15:53,285
I know two,
and I’m only eight."

282
00:15:53,285 --> 00:15:55,788
GRANNA: We are
struggling, Lord.

283
00:15:56,205 --> 00:15:59,291
We’re scared,
and we need your guidance.

284
00:15:59,291 --> 00:16:01,460
TYLER: "I learned
a new word today.

285
00:16:01,460 --> 00:16:05,965
"Medu...lloblastoma...
or something.

286
00:16:05,965 --> 00:16:08,467
,
"My mom says
I’ll be sick for a while

287
00:16:08,467 --> 00:16:09,918
but it’ll be okay."

288
00:16:13,339 --> 00:16:15,341
"Why am I sick, God?

289
00:16:15,341 --> 00:16:17,843
"The medicine stinks.

290
00:16:17,843 --> 00:16:20,346
"But I don’t have to take
my spelling test this week,

291
00:16:20,846 --> 00:16:22,681
so that’s good."

292
00:16:24,016 --> 00:16:26,518
"Can you see the stars
from heaven?

293
00:16:26,518 --> 00:16:30,022
"My dad said
You made them all.

294
00:16:30,022 --> 00:16:33,359
"I’m really glad to be
home from the hospital.

295
00:16:33,659 --> 00:16:35,744
"But most of all,

296
00:16:35,744 --> 00:16:38,247
"I really just wish
my mom would laugh.

297
00:16:38,247 --> 00:16:41,250
I miss that the most."

298
00:16:41,250 --> 00:16:42,701
GRANNA: In Jesus’ name
we pray.

299
00:16:43,085 --> 00:16:44,670
Amen.

300
00:17:10,362 --> 00:17:11,864
[Banging]

301
00:17:17,319 --> 00:17:18,904
Ahem.

302
00:17:24,793 --> 00:17:27,162
Do I have to fill out
a form or something?

303
00:17:27,329 --> 00:17:28,914
Spoken like a true
government worker.

304
00:17:29,298 --> 00:17:30,883
Yeah.

305
00:17:32,384 --> 00:17:33,802
[Sighs]

306
00:17:34,136 --> 00:17:35,220
So, you’re having
trouble

307
00:17:35,721 --> 00:17:37,172
quieting those demons
tonight?

308
00:17:37,506 --> 00:17:39,892
You having trouble
remembering you’re just
the bartender?

309
00:17:41,677 --> 00:17:44,179
You know, McDaniels,
if you keep pushing
people away--

310
00:17:44,179 --> 00:17:47,516
Save it. You’re not
my C.O. anymore.

311
00:17:51,520 --> 00:17:52,438
Ohh.

312
00:17:52,821 --> 00:17:54,406
Uhh.

313
00:17:54,406 --> 00:17:56,408
All right.

314
00:17:56,408 --> 00:17:58,410
Oh, and, Jack...

315
00:17:58,410 --> 00:18:00,412
Jimmy Buffett called.
He wants his shirt back.

316
00:18:00,412 --> 00:18:01,914
Ha!

317
00:18:02,414 --> 00:18:04,867
Michael Gleason
Singing : [Throw Me a Line]

318
00:18:04,867 --> 00:18:07,369
[Dog barking,
police siren blaring]

